```

---

## ğŸ“ Key Exam Notes (Remember This)

* `/` is the root directory
* Linux uses **forward slash `/`**
* `~` represents home directory
* Absolute path starts with `/`
* Relative path does not start with `/`

---

## âŒ Common Beginner Mistakes

âŒ Confusing `/` with `\`
âŒ Forgetting current directory
âŒ Using wrong case in names
âŒ Running commands in wrong location

âœ… Always check with `pwd`

